      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "One way your client can balance style with professionalism is to wear her hair in a neat, tidy updo that doesn't reveal too much texture or definition. A sleek, low bun or chignon is a classic choice that works well with most face shapes and hair types. Alternatively, a simple, low ponytail or sleek straightening of her hair can also be effective. When it comes to hijabs or other religious headwear, it's generally best to keep these visible, especially in more traditional or formal settings, but you may recommend that your client consider wearing a more subtle, neutral-colored headscarf that blends with her outfit. Nobody expects anyone to have to hide their identity or drop their faith, but being mindful of the power dynamics at play in a boardroom setting is key.",
